            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">2. A 47 year’s male with history of asthma came to emergency room with increasing acute shortness of breath, cough and sputum production for several days. His respiratory rate is 32/minute; diffuse expiratory wheeze and prolonged expiratory phase.<br />\nWhich of the following would used as the best indicator of severity of his asthma?</p>"
