            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">5. An HIV positive African American man admitted with history of dyspnea,dry cough and ,high LDH and paO2 of 65mmof hg.he is started on Sulphomethoxasole and trimethoprim(SMX/TMP) and prednisone. on the third day of hospital he developed severe rash and neutropenia.he has anemia and there are bite cells on peripheral smear.<br />\nWhat is the most appropriate next step in management of this patient?</p>"
