            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">73. At autopsy, a 60-year-old man is found to have a peripheral 7 cm area of golden-yellow consolidation on sectioning of the left lung. Microscopically, this area has alveoli filled with foamy macrophages.<br />\nWhich of the following conditions involving his lung is most likely to be responsible for this finding?</p>"
