            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">79. A 70-year-old woman has been bedridden for 5 weeks following a cerebrovascular accident (CVA). She has the sudden onset of dyspnea, but has no further symptoms until two days later when she experiences left sided pleuritic chest pain. A day later she suffers another CVA and dies. At autopsy, she is found to have a wedge-shaped area of hemorrhage based on the pleura of the left lower lobe. <br />\nWhich of the following pathologic findings in her pulmonary arterial branches is she most likely to have?</p>"
